How to upgrade from Windows XP
Microsoft has finally retired its 12-year-old Windows XP operating system, but there are still millions of XP computers out there. Here's what to do if you own one of them.
- Microsoft issues its final update to fix known security flaws with XP.
- After that, XP machines will still work, and you can install past security updates. You won't get new ones to address any new security flaws.